Keeping our community members healthy on every level is a high priority at Yale.

We promote health and well-being through our fitness and wellness programs and medical centers; mental health through counseling services and support groups; and spiritual health through our Chaplain’s Office, which welcomes people of every faith.
Learn how our on-campus medical facility cares for our students, staff, and faculty.
Yale Medicine’s 1,400 specialty physicians work together to provide the best care possible. We utilize advanced, innovative technology and emphasize a multidisciplinary approach.
YNHH is one of the largest medical centers in the world and among the nation’s top-ranked hospitals.
Explore the programs, resources, and services that help faculty and staff thrive.
See how we encourage our students to value their well-being and make healthier choices.
Discover the programs and facilities inside our nine-story gym, open free to all students.
Whether you are part of a particular religious/spiritual community or not, you are welcome here.
We work to keep our community members safe as they explore all our city has to offer.
We live by the motto “be prepared” and encourage our community members to do the same.
